name: Lightbulb
description:
Hum.egg 3/8

Hum.egg in copper, porcelain, clear and frosted glass

Hum.eggs is a digital collection which brings together inspiration
from jewelry craft, with special care to the
idea of the eggs created by Peter Carl Fabergé from 1885 to 1917, 
with the possibilities of the digital world, 
while experimenting with human form, mixed styles and materials,
in a contemporary design language that seeks to balance real world 
credibility while playing with the abstraction of digital scale
and material properties
